`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
Expo Router uses **typed routes** — `router.push("/settings")` fails TypeScript if `app/settings.tsx` doesn't exist. The route type is auto-generated from the file system. Creating a real screen (not a stub) is the right fix because the Settings button is a real feature that needs to navigate somewhere, and the project's "no stubs" rule prevents a placeholder.
